overview: The conversation began with the user requesting a comprehensive review
  of their sleep questionnaire application to ensure it met all specified
  acceptance criteria. The review identified several key areas needing
  improvement, categorized by priority. The subsequent implementation focused on
  addressing these gaps. High-priority items included adding a 1-10 severity
  scale for tiredness interference with safety warnings, implementing detection
  and recommendations for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA), and
  integrating logic for Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. Additionally, placeholder
  outbound links to relevant sleep and mental health resources were added to the
  report. Weighted scoring for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) was also
  implemented to provide a more accurate assessment. The plan was executed
  systematically, with each identified gap being addressed in the application's
  codebase, including updates to types, validation schemas, UI components, and
  report generation logic.
